Tech companies display demo screens showing their latest apps, and a startup founder invites students to a lunchtime pitch session. A robotics startup attracts attention by flying a small drone above its booth, and a data science company showcases a live dashboard of fair attendance. Workshops on networking etiquette begin in an adjoining classroom. As the day winds down, interview sign-up sheets fill with names. Meanwhile, friends decompress on the quad, comparing responses from various companies.

Nearby, consulting firms have stacked glossy case study booklets on high tables. Dozens of booths with colorful banners circle the polished floor. At the entrance, event staff scan registrations and hand out lanyards.
